Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the rice. When boiling, add the @basmati rice{150} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} in a large (preferably ovenproof) #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and season with @salt and @pepper. Cook until golden on the outside, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

While the chicken cooks, trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice. Pop the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} in a #bowl{} and add the oil, stir well.

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Once the chicken is browned, add the leek and @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan.

> TIP: Add a splash more oil if needed.

Cook until the mushrooms have browned and the leek softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Once the veggies are soft and chicken is cooked, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @chicken stock powder{1}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Bring to a boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. If your pan isn't ovenproof, pop in an #oven dish{} now. Sprinkle over the cheesy breadcrumbs and then grill until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}. Serve in #bowls{} with the chicken crumble on top. Enjoy!